"Trenberth K.E.","An imperative for climate change planning: tracking Earth's global energy",2009,"Current Opinion in Environmental Sustainability","1","1",,"19","27",,,10.1016/j.cosust.2009.06.001,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-70449334393&partnerID=40&md5=2a8609ab25593a026bbfa811776e4f1b","National Center for Atmospheric Research1, P.O. Box 3000, Boulder, CO 80307-3000, United States","Trenberth, K.E., National Center for Atmospheric Research1, P.O. Box 3000, Boulder, CO 80307-3000, United States","Planned adaptation to climate change requires information about what is happening and why. While a long-term trend is for global warming, short-term periods of cooling can occur and have physical causes associated with natural variability. However, such natural variability means that energy is rearranged or changed within the climate system, and should be traceable. An assessment is given of our ability to track changes in reservoirs and flows of energy within the climate system. Arguments are given that developing the ability to do this is important, as it affects interpretations of global and especially regional climate change, and prospects for the future. © 2009 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.",,"adaptive management; climate change; cooling; energy flow; environmental planning; future prospect; regional climate; tracking",,,,,,"Easterling, D.R., Wehner MF, Is the climate warming or cooling? (2009) Geophys Res Lett, 36, pp. L08706. , 10.1029/2009GL037810; (2007) IPCC: Climate Change 2007: The Physical Science Basis, pp. 996 pp.. , Solomon S., Qin D., Manning M., Chen Z., Marquis M., Averyt K.B., Tignor M., and Miller H.L. (Eds), Cambridge Univ Press. This is the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change Fourth Assessment Report (AR4) that provides a comprehensive review of climate change up to about 2005; Kopp, G., Lawrence, G., Rottman, G., The total irradiance monitor (TIM): science results (2005) Solar Phys, 230, pp. 129-140; Fröhlich, C., 